The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Saturday, February 14, 2004 				 ITC plan
																								Calcutta, Feb. 13: The infotech subsidiary of ITC  ITC Infotech  is considering setting up a business process outsourcing centre in Calcutta, says a staff reporter.																								ITC chairman Y.C. Deveshwar met chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee today and discussed the infotech divisions future plans in the state.																								ITC Infotech will set up a BPO unit here and the company chairman informed the chief minister of this, Bengal IT minister Manab Mukherjee said.																								The company has a small outsourcing unit at its sprawling 36-acre Infotechpark in Bangalore. 																								Mukherjee said the government will extend co-operation to the company. We always wanted big players to set up operations in Calcutta. Its good that ITC Infotech has selected Calcutta for its second BPO centre. We have asked them to give us details of what they want from us, he said.																								The ITC chairman, however, did not divulge much about his meeting with Bhattacharjee. I discussed our companys expansion plans in IT-enabled services business, said Deveshwar.
